Paper: hep-th/0111146

Date: 2001-11-15

Title: Non-Abelian Thermal Large Gauge Transformations in 2+1 Dimensions

Authors: F. T. Brandt, Ashok Das, Gerald V. Dunne, J. Frenkel and J. C. Taylor

Comments: 10 pages, revtex

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D65 (2002) 065006

We discuss several different constructions of non-Abelian large gaugetransformations at finite temperature. Pisarski's ansatz with even windingnumber is related to Hopf mappings, and we present a simple new ansatz that hasany integer winding number at finite temperature.